  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research settings to predict hemolysis in centrifugal blood pumps under ventricular assist device operating conditions. The CFD hemolysis model for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump was assessed under a Minimal profile submission. All 13 credibility factors were reviewed; seven were formally assessed and six flagged as epistemic gaps at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across the operating envelope. Despite gaps in several credibility factors, the assessment team determined that the model provides sufficient evidence to support the intended regulatory submission under the Minimal profile requirements. This package does not carry a structured Context of Use record; the intended-use scope is understood from the surrounding clinical research context in which the model has been deployed.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-absolute-prediction-claim-001",
